VALUES
  ('b3b50b79-2b3b-4b37-a9b5-7a57b6c2bb2b','becddbcf-bcef-4bb1-80b9-95fed0635545',29.0,'owner ~48 (<53 band — early exit window low), +4 long-tenure 47yr',70.0,'multi-staff (30 emp) 47yr tenure — solid SBA-financeable book',67.0,'2 coasting tells: same shop 1970s-90s (long-tenure tell); tell: no certifications',82.0,'Metro=Austin; nudge +5 (semicon/aerospace). SBA-financeable buyer access typical.',59.0,'C_watch','Waggoner Manufacturing Inc. (Round Rock, TX) — 47yr CNC shop, owner ~48. L1=29 | L2=70 | L3=67 | L4=82 -> final=59 (C_watch). Coasting tells: 2 matched. Enrichment note: B/A-tier. Family-business 3rd-gen runway gives 5-10 yr exit horizon (vs the 12-36mo solo-owner target). Watch for 4th gen development or sibling-coowner setup.','certification uplift (ISO 9001 / AS9100) opens aerospace book and lifts margin.','medium',0.85),
  ('48be9f9e-06e0-4204-97ff-b4b5e69a91f4','becddbcf-bcef-4bb1-80b9-95fed0635545',25.0,'owner ~50 (<53 band — early exit window low)',70.0,'multi-staff (10 emp) 19yr tenure — solid SBA-financeable book',67.0,'2 coasting tells: dated website / pre-2015 era; tell: no certifications',82.0,'Metro=Austin; nudge +5 (semicon/aerospace). SBA-financeable buyer access typical.',57.0,'C_watch','Austin Precision Machining and Manufacturing (APMM) (Pflugerville, TX) — 19yr CNC shop, owner ~50. L1=25 | L2=70 | L3=67 | L4=82 -> final=57 (C_watch). Coasting tells: 2 matched. Enrichment note: C-tier candidate. Owner too young + still growing → NOT a 12-36 month seller. Score low for time-to-exit but keep in long-tail watch list.','certification uplift (ISO 9001 / AS9100) opens aerospace book and lifts margin.','medium',0.55),
  ('ffdb74b8-3da0-45aa-ab96-88714b114509','becddbcf-bcef-4bb1-80b9-95fed0635545',51.0,'owner ~55 (53-57 band), +4 long-tenure 28yr',85.0,'multi-staff (80 emp) 28yr tenure — solid SBA-financeable book; AS9100 +10 (aerospace premium), ISO 9001 +5',42.0,'1 coasting tell: same shop 1970s-90s (long-tenure tell)',50.0,'Metro=Rural; nudge -3. SBA-financeable buyer access typical.',57.0,'C_watch','KALCO Machine & Manufacturing (Wichita Falls, TX) — 28yr CNC shop, owner ~55. L1=51 | L2=85 | L3=42 | L4=50 -> final=57 (C_watch). Certs: ISO 9001, AS9100. Coasting tells: 1 matched. Enrichment note: SIZE FLAG: 130,000+ sqft + AS9100 + multi-industry suggests revenue may exceed $30M small-biz ceiling. KEPT pending Comptroller sales-data check. Owner age estimated from founder cohort assumption (founder age 27-30 at 1998 launch → 55-58 today).','diversify into aerospace/defense/medical to de-risk single-cycle exposure.','medium',0.55),
  ('758ad5ed-beaf-4d71-be3c-63f59eb57b8a','becddbcf-bcef-4bb1-80b9-95fed0635545',29.0,'owner ~50 (<53 band — early exit window low), +4 long-tenure 26yr',62.0,'solo/small-team 26yr — SBA-financeable but thin',67.0,'2 coasting tells: social media absent; tell: no certifications',78.0,'Metro=San Antonio; nudge +3 (aerospace/defense Kelly AFB). SBA-financeable buyer access typical.',56.0,'C_watch','JB Machine LLC (San Antonio, TX) — 26yr CNC shop, owner ~50. L1=29 | L2=62 | L3=67 | L4=78 -> final=56 (C_watch). Coasting tells: 2 matched. Enrichment note: Strong B/A candidate. Owner-led, low marketing investment, San Antonio defense corridor = classic coasting-with-real-customers. Investigate via TX SOS franchise filings to get full owner name.','certification uplift (ISO 9001 / AS9100) opens aerospace book and lifts margin.','medium',0.45),
  ('73dd5103-6bbe-4421-ad14-b755e9813c4c','becddbcf-bcef-4bb1-80b9-95fed0635545',25.0,'owner ~50 (<53 band — early exit window low)',62.0,'solo/small-team 21yr — SBA-financeable but thin',67.0,'2 coasting tells: owner-operator / founder still active; tell: no certifications',88.0,'Metro=DFW; nudge +5 (Lockheed/Bell aerospace + general industrial). SBA-financeable buyer access typical.',56.0,'C_watch','JY''s Extreme Machine LLC (Burleson, TX) — 21yr CNC shop, owner ~50. L1=25 | L2=62 | L3=67 | L4=88 -> final=56 (C_watch). Coasting tells: 2 matched. Enrichment note: B-tier (small). Too small for typical PE roll-up but ideal solo-acquirer bolt-on. Jason''s explicit generational-decline concern in marketing copy is a SUCCESSION SIGNAL — he''s thinking about exit.','certification uplift (ISO 9001 / AS9100) opens aerospace book and lifts margin.','medium',0.78),
